properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued January 15 at 7:10PM MST until January 18 at 2:00AM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 35 to 45 mph with gusts up to 65 mph
possible.

* WHERE...East Platte County, Goshen County, Laramie Valley,
Central Laramie County and Eastern Laramie County to the
nebraska state line. This includes I-25 near Wyo Hill as well as
the cities of Cheyenne and Laramie.

* WHEN...From Friday morning through late Friday night.

* IMPACTS...Mainly to transportation. Travel could be difficult,
especially for high profile vehicles with strong crosswinds. Use
caution if you are driving. Secure loose outdoor items as they
may be blown and damaged.
properties.instruction:
Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates on this
situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a safe
location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE FRIDAY NIGHT
